Aneka Tambang, CIMB Niaga, Unilever: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-29T01:38:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/aneka-tambang-cimb-niaga-unilever-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  slipped 0.1 percent to
3,602.86.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ): Nickel for three-month delivery
declined 3.1 percent to $26,220 a metric ton in  London 
yesterday, the steepest drop since March 15. Aneka, Indonesia’s
second-largest nickel producer, was unchanged at 2,250 rupiah.  PT Bank CIMB Niaga (BNGA IJ): CIMB Niaga shareholders
decided the bank won’t pay a dividend from last year’s earnings
to maintain a capital adequacy ratio of 14 percent as it plans
to boost lending,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing President
Director Arwin Rasyid. CIMB Niaga, a unit of  Malaysia ’s CIMB
Group Holdings Bhd., was unchanged at 1,720 rupiah.  PT International Nickel Indonesia (INCO IJ): The company’s
2010 net income rose to $437.4 million from $170.4 million a
year earlier, it said in a statement to the stock exchange. That
compares with a $415 million mean estimate of 16 analysts in a
Bloomberg News survey. PT Inco, as  Indonesia ’s biggest nickel
producer is also known, was unchanged at 4,750 rupiah.  PT Unilever Indonesia (UNVR IJ): The company’s 2010 net
income rose to 3.39 trillion rupiah ($389 million) from 3.04
trillion rupiah a year earlier, Unilever said in a statement
published in Investor Daily Indonesia. That compares with a 3.6
trillion rupiah mean estimate of 18 analysts in a Bloomberg News
survey. Unilever, Indonesia’s largest detergent maker, declined
1.6 percent to 15,750 rupiah.  PT United Tractors (UNTR IJ): Indonesia’s biggest heavy
equipment seller was rated “neutral” in new coverage at
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. The brokerage has a share-price
forecast of 24,000 rupiah, analysts led by Miang Chuen Koh wrote
in a report. United Tractors fell 1.6 percent to 22,200 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  